properties.name: CidrBlock
properties.description: The IPv4 CIDR range to allow or deny, in CIDR notation (for example, 172.16.0.0/24). Requirement is conditional: You must specify the CidrBlock or Ipv6CidrBlock property

type.description: The IPv4 CIDR range to allow or deny, in CIDR notation (for example, 172.16.0.0/24). Requirement is conditional: You must specify the CidrBlock or Ipv6CidrBlock property

properties.name: Egress
properties.description: Indicates whether this is an egress rule (rule is applied to traffic leaving the subnet)

type.description: Indicates whether this is an egress rule (rule is applied to traffic leaving the subnet)

properties.name: Icmp
properties.description: The Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) code and type. Requirement is conditional: Required if specifying 1 (ICMP) for the protocol parameter

type.description: The Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) code and type. Requirement is conditional: Required if specifying 1 (ICMP) for the protocol parameter

properties.name: Ipv6CidrBlock
properties.description: The IPv6 network range to allow or deny, in CIDR notation (for example 2001:db8:1234:1a00::/64)

type.description: The IPv6 network range to allow or deny, in CIDR notation (for example 2001:db8:1234:1a00::/64)

properties.name: NetworkAclId
properties.description: The ID of the network ACL

type.description: The ID of the network ACL

properties.name: PortRange
properties.description: The IPv4 network range to allow or deny, in CIDR notation (for example 172.16.0.0/24). We modify the specified CIDR block to its canonical form; for example, if you specify 100.68.0.18/18, we modify it to 100.68.0.0/18

type.description: The IPv4 network range to allow or deny, in CIDR notation (for example 172.16.0.0/24). We modify the specified CIDR block to its canonical form; for example, if you specify 100.68.0.18/18, we modify it to 100.68.0.0/18

properties.name: Protocol
properties.description: The protocol number. A value of "-1" means all protocols. If you specify "-1" or a protocol number other than "6" (TCP), "17" (UDP), or "1" (ICMP), traffic on all ports is allowed, regardless of any ports or ICMP types or codes that you specify. If you specify protocol "58" (ICMPv6) and specify an IPv4 CIDR block, traffic for all ICMP types and codes allowed, regardless of any that you specify. If you specify protocol "58" (ICMPv6) and specify an IPv6 CIDR block, you must specify an ICMP type and code

type.description: The protocol number. A value of "-1" means all protocols. If you specify "-1" or a protocol number other than "6" (TCP), "17" (UDP), or "1" (ICMP), traffic on all ports is allowed, regardless of any ports or ICMP types or codes that you specify. If you specify protocol "58" (ICMPv6) and specify an IPv4 CIDR block, traffic for all ICMP types and codes allowed, regardless of any that you specify. If you specify protocol "58" (ICMPv6) and specify an IPv6 CIDR block, you must specify an ICMP type and code

properties.name: RuleAction
properties.description: Indicates whether to allow or deny the traffic that matches the rule

type.description: Indicates whether to allow or deny the traffic that matches the rule

properties.name: RuleNumber
properties.description: Rule number to assign to the entry, such as 100. ACL entries are processed in ascending order by rule number. Entries can't use the same rule number unless one is an egress rule and the other is an ingress rule

type.description: Rule number to assign to the entry, such as 100. ACL entries are processed in ascending order by rule number. Entries can't use the same rule number unless one is an egress rule and the other is an ingress rule
